1
00:00:51,234 --> 00:00:52,824
I hope it’s always like this.

2
00:00:53,025 --> 00:00:56,404
We can prevent the tragedy
before it happens.

3
00:00:56,598 --> 00:00:57,598
Luthor?

4
00:00:58,308 --> 00:00:59,726
What are you doing here?

5
00:01:01,686 --> 00:01:04,522
Well, I'm obviously here
to check on my brother.

6
00:01:05,482 --> 00:01:06,691
How's he holding up?

7
00:01:06,858 --> 00:01:07,984
Hey, don't worry.

8
00:01:09,319 --> 00:01:10,319
Don't worry.

9
00:01:12,530 --> 00:01:13,690
Theodore doesn't mind.

10
00:01:13,715 --> 00:01:16,217
You’ve killed so many fellow students.

11
00:01:20,246 --> 00:01:22,082
It’s the Pandora’s box.

12
00:01:22,749 --> 00:01:24,459
Once what’s inside this leaks,

13
00:01:25,251 --> 00:01:28,004
the campus will definitely be in chaos.

14
00:01:28,213 --> 00:01:29,756
I'm Lorelei Rios.

15
00:01:30,924 --> 00:01:33,718
And I’m speaking
on behalf of the Q.E.D. Club.

16
00:01:34,511 --> 00:01:36,054
I know you, Lorelei.

17
00:01:36,513 --> 00:01:38,264
I’m Emeraude Emerson,

18
00:01:38,264 --> 00:01:39,933
the Student Council President.

19
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:43,520
I just heard you made a deal
with the Student Council.

20
00:01:43,812 --> 00:01:47,023
They say you have
some very scandalous files?

21
00:01:49,609 --> 00:01:50,860
Impressive.

22
00:02:00,411 --> 00:02:01,411
Jamie?

23
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:06,000
Good morning, Lorelei!

24
00:02:06,584 --> 00:02:08,211
Did you sleep well?

25
00:02:15,009 --> 00:02:16,761
Are you ready for breakfast?

26
00:02:18,805 --> 00:02:21,266
I prepared meals for three.

27
00:02:22,684 --> 00:02:25,186
Wait, where am I?

28
00:02:26,869 --> 00:02:28,663
You're in the right apartment.

29
00:02:29,463 --> 00:02:31,620
You must be surprised that I’m here.

30
00:02:37,073 --> 00:02:39,576
Loki let me in last night
when you were asleep.

31
00:02:39,952 --> 00:02:40,952
Last night?

32
00:02:41,452 --> 00:02:44,080
So you slept here?

33
00:02:44,448 --> 00:02:46,001
You think I'd sleep outside?

34
00:02:47,130 --> 00:02:51,274
Actually, I think I’ll just stay here.

35
00:02:51,299 --> 00:02:53,676
So I can always be with Loki.

36
00:02:54,193 --> 00:02:56,154
Do you think that’s a good idea?

37
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:04,142
Loki, dear!

38
00:03:04,647 --> 00:03:06,815
Good morning!

39
00:03:10,899 --> 00:03:12,521
You two seem to be getting along.

40
00:03:13,026 --> 00:03:14,027
Wow.

41
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:16,446
It's like a newly live-in couple.

42
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:19,938
Were you surprised
Jamie’s here in our apartment?

43
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:22,327
Just so you know,

44
00:03:22,420 --> 00:03:24,764
she begged to stay here until sunrise.

45
00:03:25,830 --> 00:03:28,541
So where did she sleep here?

46
00:03:30,321 --> 00:03:32,574
I offered our cozy couch to her.

47
00:03:33,020 --> 00:03:35,355
But she insisted on
sleeping in my room.

48
00:03:36,090 --> 00:03:39,142
You know I can be pretty persistent.

49
00:03:39,196 --> 00:03:42,699
Persuasion is one of my strongest
suits after all.

50
00:03:44,182 --> 00:03:45,433
Wait, so...

51
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:47,018
Let me get this straight.

52
00:03:47,518 --> 00:03:50,438
She slept in your bed,

53
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:54,067
and you slept on the floor?

54
00:03:57,237 --> 00:03:58,696
Why would I sleep on the floor?

55
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:00,280
That’s my room.

56
00:04:01,783 --> 00:04:03,201
We just shared the same bed.

57
00:04:03,618 --> 00:04:05,370
You two slept together?

58
00:04:06,177 --> 00:04:07,428
Is there a problem with that?

59
00:04:08,253 --> 00:04:13,011
Is there a law against a man
and a woman sharing a bed?

60
00:04:14,279 --> 00:04:16,072
Do you know what happened last night?

61
00:04:18,383 --> 00:04:21,135
It was quite fun, actually.

62
00:04:22,178 --> 00:04:23,178
You know what,

63
00:04:24,013 --> 00:04:26,015
I don’t need to know all the details.

64
00:04:31,584 --> 00:04:32,584
Oops.

65
00:04:36,484 --> 00:04:38,152
Shadows

66
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:41,781
In the dark are crawling

67
00:04:42,490 --> 00:04:46,536
Keeping watch and barring your way

68
00:04:46,536 --> 00:04:50,081
As if the line could not be crossed

69
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:54,627
To every scream and every tremor

70
00:04:54,627 --> 00:04:57,797
These walls remain the only witness

71
00:04:57,797 --> 00:05:00,758
Every noise is etched in here

72
00:05:00,758 --> 00:05:05,263
Like fire and ammunition for your memory

73
00:05:06,639 --> 00:05:08,766
Heed the warnings

74
00:05:10,018 --> 00:05:12,395
The threats poised to strike

75
00:05:13,479 --> 00:05:17,150
For this world

76
00:05:17,817 --> 00:05:20,445
is not what you imagined

77
00:05:20,445 --> 00:05:22,905
Heed the warnings

78
00:05:23,906 --> 00:05:26,034
Open up your eyes

79
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:30,872
For this world

80
00:05:31,581 --> 00:05:34,125
is not what you imagined

81
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:38,963
Heed the warnings

82
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:49,098
Oh, Lori! You got dressed fast.

83
00:05:49,249 --> 00:05:50,491
Why are you such in a hurry?

84
00:05:50,806 --> 00:05:53,034
Why don't you wait for Jamie,
so you can go to school together?

85
00:05:53,059 --> 00:05:55,645
I still have a lot to do.
I need to go ahead.

86
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:00,276
What’s with her?

87
00:06:10,411 --> 00:06:13,664
Lori, my BFF! Oh, my gosh!

88
00:06:13,689 --> 00:06:15,066
Have you heard?

89
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:17,502
- What’s up? What is it?
- Have you heard the gossip?

90
00:06:17,752 --> 00:06:18,752
What is it?

91
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:20,343
Here's the thing.

92
00:06:20,504 --> 00:06:23,139
I passed by the faculty room earlier,

93
00:06:23,164 --> 00:06:26,751
and I saw our adviser
talking to a male student.

94
00:06:27,178 --> 00:06:28,221
At first,

95
00:06:28,596 --> 00:06:31,015
I didn’t pay too much attention.

96
00:06:31,182 --> 00:06:32,182
But...

97
00:06:32,308 --> 00:06:35,103
looks like he's getting transferred
to our block.

98
00:06:35,728 --> 00:06:37,688
In the middle of the semester?

99
00:06:38,155 --> 00:06:40,491
So that’s allowed at Clark University?

100
00:06:40,549 --> 00:06:43,427
Maybe that student’s
a special case because...

101
00:06:43,569 --> 00:06:45,446
he looks like he comes from a rich family.

102
00:06:45,793 --> 00:06:48,462
Plus, he's good-looking.

103
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:50,535
He's got a killer smile.

104
00:06:50,701 --> 00:06:53,037
Looks physically fit.

105
00:06:53,062 --> 00:06:56,566
He's got charisma. So handsome!

106
00:06:57,041 --> 00:06:58,709
I thought it was something serious.

107
00:06:59,293 --> 00:07:00,670
Aren't you excited?

108
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:03,005
Why would I be excited?

109
00:07:03,172 --> 00:07:06,217
It’s not like meeting him
would change my life.

110
00:07:06,442 --> 00:07:10,234
Huh? There are barely any
good-looking guys here at Clark University!

111
00:07:10,638 --> 00:07:13,057
And the ones who are,
they like good-looking guys too!

112
00:07:15,425 --> 00:07:17,145
Uh... Good morning, everyone!

113
00:07:17,228 --> 00:07:18,828
- Good morning, sir!
- Good morning, sir!

114
00:07:19,564 --> 00:07:20,940
Sorry for the interruption.

115
00:07:21,315 --> 00:07:24,986
I would just like to introduce to you
your newest schoolmate.

116
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:27,280
A transferee student.

117
00:07:28,322 --> 00:07:30,700
Please come in and introduce yourself.

118
00:07:33,911 --> 00:07:34,911
Al?

119
00:07:36,164 --> 00:07:38,749
Good morning, everyone!
I'm Alistair Ravena.

120
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:42,048
Pleased to meet you all,
but you can call me Ali.

121
00:07:42,753 --> 00:07:45,840
Well, Alistair is a B.A. Pol Sci student,

122
00:07:45,882 --> 00:07:47,758
who recently transferred here

123
00:07:47,783 --> 00:07:49,994
from St. Bartholomew College in Manila.

124
00:07:50,219 --> 00:07:52,016
And, guys, do me a favor. Please.

125
00:07:52,388 --> 00:07:53,890
Please good to him, okay?

126
00:07:54,891 --> 00:07:56,684
You may wanna sit behind of...

127
00:07:57,351 --> 00:07:58,394
What’s your name again?

128
00:07:58,716 --> 00:08:00,271
Miss Rios, right?

129
00:08:01,355 --> 00:08:02,355
See you around!

130
00:08:25,338 --> 00:08:27,464
So, where did you study again?

131
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,800
St. Bartholomew College in Manila.

132
00:08:29,825 --> 00:08:32,245
St. Bartholomew College?

133
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:33,679
St. Barth’s?

134
00:08:33,748 --> 00:08:35,691
Didn’t we have a classmate from there?

135
00:08:35,740 --> 00:08:37,074
It sounds familiar.

136
00:08:37,099 --> 00:08:38,142
I think, it's Lori.

137
00:08:38,167 --> 00:08:39,669
Wasn’t she also from Manila?

138
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:42,062
Right?

139
00:08:44,524 --> 00:08:45,524
Excuse me. Hi!

140
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:47,902
Al, we need to talk.

141
00:08:49,237 --> 00:08:50,404
- Okay.
- Let's go.

142
00:08:51,447 --> 00:08:52,896
Wait, BFF!

143
00:08:53,007 --> 00:08:54,759
BFF, where are you taking him?

144
00:08:54,784 --> 00:08:58,412
- We’re not done with him yet!
- Lori is so aggressive.

145
00:08:58,437 --> 00:09:01,750
Guys, Al is really handsome!

146
00:09:01,775 --> 00:09:02,901
Get in line!

147
00:09:03,911 --> 00:09:07,206
Lori, is this really how you plan
to greet me?

148
00:09:08,525 --> 00:09:11,695
You didn’t even acknowledge me
when I came into class.

149
00:09:12,301 --> 00:09:15,471
Sorry, I just didn’t know how to react.

150
00:09:16,847 --> 00:09:18,140
But, first things first...

151
00:09:19,016 --> 00:09:20,393
what are you doing here?

152
00:09:21,352 --> 00:09:22,853
Did Papa send you?

153
00:09:23,938 --> 00:09:26,357
What do you think I am, a lapdog?

154
00:09:26,672 --> 00:09:28,799
I’m not here under anyone’s orders.

155
00:09:29,563 --> 00:09:31,440
I’m here because of you, okay?

156
00:09:38,369 --> 00:09:39,704
Because of me?

157
00:09:40,803 --> 00:09:42,627
Ever since I watched that video…

158
00:09:44,284 --> 00:09:46,787
I got so much worried about you, Lori.

159
00:09:47,748 --> 00:09:50,668
I thought you’d be in danger,
being with that detective guy.

160
00:09:51,524 --> 00:09:52,692
Look, I just want to make sure

161
00:09:52,717 --> 00:09:54,844
what happened to you before
doesn’t happen again.

162
00:09:57,847 --> 00:09:59,765
So you’re here to protect me?

163
00:10:01,559 --> 00:10:02,559
Again?

164
00:10:03,484 --> 00:10:04,868
As always, Lori.

165
00:10:07,064 --> 00:10:08,482
By the way...

166
00:10:08,889 --> 00:10:11,141
how’s that detective boyfriend of yours?

167
00:10:11,736 --> 00:10:12,862
Loki, right?

168
00:10:13,237 --> 00:10:15,406
It’s been so long
since I last saw him.

169
00:10:16,252 --> 00:10:19,093
Well, he’s been indefinitely suspended

170
00:10:19,118 --> 00:10:20,453
by the school admin.

171
00:10:21,637 --> 00:10:22,637
Too bad.

172
00:10:23,025 --> 00:10:24,743
I was looking forward to meet him again.

173
00:10:29,228 --> 00:10:31,522
- Oh, handsome!
- I know!

174
00:10:31,547 --> 00:10:33,299
- Close?
- They seem to know each other.

175
00:10:33,424 --> 00:10:34,634
Let’s transfer.

176
00:10:35,259 --> 00:10:37,178
Your fan club won’t stop bothering you.

177
00:10:41,182 --> 00:10:43,893
Oh, my God!

178
00:10:45,234 --> 00:10:46,235
Oh, I know.

179
00:10:46,260 --> 00:10:48,846
Why don’t you just give me a tour
of your Q.E.D. clubroom?

180
00:10:53,235 --> 00:10:55,154
Sure. Why not?

181
00:10:56,906 --> 00:10:58,157
- Let’s go.
- Come on.

182
00:11:08,417 --> 00:11:09,417
Thanks.

183
00:11:18,678 --> 00:11:20,930
So this is where your adventures
started, huh?

184
00:11:22,932 --> 00:11:24,308
How many members are you again?

185
00:11:26,644 --> 00:11:27,812
We’re only three.

186
00:11:28,896 --> 00:11:31,190
Loki,

187
00:11:31,649 --> 00:11:33,317
Jamie, and me.

188
00:11:34,402 --> 00:11:38,155
We usually take on
a lot of clients, but...

189
00:11:38,489 --> 00:11:40,624
as of recent, not so much.

190
00:11:43,828 --> 00:11:44,828
Okay.

191
00:11:47,957 --> 00:11:50,543
- The things written in your blog--
- Wait!

192
00:11:50,918 --> 00:11:52,294
You’ve read my blog?

193
00:11:53,331 --> 00:11:55,291
Well, yeah. Just recently.

194
00:11:56,338 --> 00:11:59,758
Is what happened in the video
related to one of your cases?

195
00:12:00,469 --> 00:12:01,721
Because for me,

196
00:12:01,746 --> 00:12:04,790
Loki doesn’t seem like someone
who would assault anyone for no reason.

197
00:12:09,437 --> 00:12:10,646
It’s a long story.

198
00:12:12,314 --> 00:12:15,484
But it all started,
when last year,

199
00:12:15,918 --> 00:12:18,379
Loki’s only friend, Rhea,

200
00:12:18,404 --> 00:12:22,366
was killed by a man
only known as Moriarty.

201
00:12:23,075 --> 00:12:24,827
And Stein Alberts,

202
00:12:25,244 --> 00:12:28,164
the guy Loki assaulted in the video...

203
00:12:29,198 --> 00:12:31,950
identified himself as Moriarty.

204
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:41,385
Now I understand why he did that.

205
00:12:42,303 --> 00:12:43,888
That was a natural response.

206
00:12:45,585 --> 00:12:47,212
Still, that’s not right.

207
00:12:47,950 --> 00:12:50,244
He should’ve just let justice
take its course

208
00:12:50,269 --> 00:12:51,896
and gone through due process.

209
00:12:52,796 --> 00:12:55,382
And because of that,
he got into more trouble.

210
00:12:57,943 --> 00:12:59,987
But no one believes him.

211
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:02,798
We couldn't find any evidence

212
00:13:02,823 --> 00:13:05,284
to prove that Stein is, in fact, Moriarty.

213
00:13:06,118 --> 00:13:08,412
Even though he himself told us.

214
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:10,748
I really thought we had him.

215
00:13:12,541 --> 00:13:13,876
So...

216
00:13:15,836 --> 00:13:18,589
That means once Stein
wakes up from his coma,

217
00:13:20,466 --> 00:13:22,593
he could come after Loki and you
for revenge?

218
00:13:23,427 --> 00:13:24,427
It's possible.

219
00:13:32,394 --> 00:13:34,274
You only have three members
in your club, right?

220
00:13:35,231 --> 00:13:36,857
Do you mind if you add another one?

221
00:13:38,257 --> 00:13:39,717
I want to join your club.

222
00:13:40,694 --> 00:13:41,694
What?

223
00:13:41,946 --> 00:13:43,072
Are you serious?

224
00:13:43,239 --> 00:13:45,699
Well, yeah.
That’s the only way I can protect you.

225
00:13:47,388 --> 00:13:49,678
And for sure,
you have a lot of dangerous cases.

226
00:13:49,703 --> 00:13:51,497
I don’t want you
to get into trouble again.

227
00:13:51,724 --> 00:13:53,601
I don’t need your protection, Al.

228
00:13:53,644 --> 00:13:56,762
But I’m also interested in mysteries,
just like you.

229
00:13:57,086 --> 00:13:58,754
Is that enough reason?

230
00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:02,841
Look,

231
00:14:03,092 --> 00:14:04,885
I have to inform Loki first.

232
00:14:05,219 --> 00:14:07,012
Right, as club president,

233
00:14:07,037 --> 00:14:10,663
only he has the right
between the two of us to accept new--

234
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:15,855
Good afternoon, Lori!

235
00:14:15,896 --> 00:14:17,189
Do you still remember me?

236
00:14:17,214 --> 00:14:19,383
Yes! Of course!
Agatha, please come in!

237
00:14:22,378 --> 00:14:23,379
Oh!

238
00:14:23,404 --> 00:14:25,406
Agatha, this is Alistair Ravena,

239
00:14:25,431 --> 00:14:27,391
an applicant of the Q.E.D. Club.

240
00:14:27,616 --> 00:14:31,787
Al, this is Agatha Cortez,
our literary editor at The Clarion.

241
00:14:31,929 --> 00:14:33,138
- Hi.
- Nice to meet you, Agatha.

242
00:14:33,163 --> 00:14:35,566
- Nice to meet you.
- Please, let’s have a seat.

243
00:14:38,346 --> 00:14:40,640
So, what brings you here?

244
00:14:41,088 --> 00:14:43,966
Can the Q.E.D. Club help you again?

245
00:14:44,273 --> 00:14:46,260
First things first,
I wanted to let you know

246
00:14:46,285 --> 00:14:50,640
that the draft of the literary folio
featuring your blogs is finished.

247
00:14:50,733 --> 00:14:52,616
So, I wanted to show you first

248
00:14:52,641 --> 00:14:54,852
before we send it to the printing press.

249
00:14:55,625 --> 00:14:56,625
Oh!

250
00:14:59,648 --> 00:15:00,983
Wow!

251
00:15:01,275 --> 00:15:03,068
Congrats! You're amazing!

252
00:15:03,379 --> 00:15:04,379
Thanks!

253
00:15:04,649 --> 00:15:05,817
I can’t believe it.

254
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:06,905
Wow, Lori.

255
00:15:06,989 --> 00:15:09,325
You really deserve to be in the folio.

256
00:15:09,686 --> 00:15:10,896
Thanks, Agatha!

257
00:15:12,562 --> 00:15:16,816
Actually, I wanted to
bring a case to you.

258
00:15:17,884 --> 00:15:18,927
Oh, no.

259
00:15:19,810 --> 00:15:21,770
Ever since Loki has been gone,

260
00:15:21,795 --> 00:15:23,797
we haven’t been accepting cases.

261
00:15:25,297 --> 00:15:26,297
Is that so?

262
00:15:26,817 --> 00:15:28,861
But you can tell me.

263
00:15:28,886 --> 00:15:30,763
So when he gets back,
we can solve it.

264
00:15:31,513 --> 00:15:32,950
Really? Okay.

265
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:35,434
Can you come with me
to The Clarion's office?

266
00:15:45,069 --> 00:15:48,948
Can this count as my qualifying exam
for the Q.E.D.?

267
00:15:49,907 --> 00:15:51,283
Sure, but...

268
00:15:51,825 --> 00:15:56,038
it'd be better if Loki were here
to see your performance himself.

269
00:15:56,455 --> 00:15:58,540
Don’t worry. I won’t let you down.

270
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:02,419
Okay. Let's go.

271
00:16:13,180 --> 00:16:14,598
- Gus?
- Yes?

272
00:16:14,598 --> 00:16:16,350
The Q.E.D. Club members are here.

273
00:16:16,375 --> 00:16:17,418
Alright. Hold on.

274
00:16:22,439 --> 00:16:23,439
Welcome!

275
00:16:23,797 --> 00:16:24,817
I’ve been expecting you!

276
00:16:24,842 --> 00:16:27,803
Actually, I’m pleased to finally meet you
face-to-face, Miss Lorelei.

277
00:16:28,195 --> 00:16:30,698
I’ve been an avid reader of your blog.

278
00:16:30,839 --> 00:16:32,507
Oh, sorry. Where are my manners?

279
00:16:32,821 --> 00:16:35,824
My name’s Augustus Moran.
But you can call me Gus.

280
00:16:37,329 --> 00:16:39,248
It’s a pleasure to meet you too, Gus.

281
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:41,291
Yeah, and...

282
00:16:42,334 --> 00:16:43,334
This is?

283
00:16:45,834 --> 00:16:46,855
Okay.

284
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:48,549
You’re not Loki, right?

285
00:16:49,091 --> 00:16:50,884
I heard his hair is a little bit…

286
00:16:52,219 --> 00:16:53,219
unkempt.

287
00:16:53,721 --> 00:16:54,721
You’re right.

288
00:16:55,597 --> 00:16:56,807
I’m Alistair Ravena.

289
00:16:58,058 --> 00:16:59,435
Q.E.D. Club applicant.

290
00:17:00,060 --> 00:17:01,060
Pleased to meet you.

291
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:02,813
Likewise. Pleasure is mine.

292
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:04,732
- Alright! Come on in, guys!
- Yeah.

293
00:17:05,733 --> 00:17:06,733
Okay.

294
00:17:07,860 --> 00:17:08,860
Take a seat.

295
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:14,283
As you know by now,

296
00:17:14,658 --> 00:17:18,287
we’ve been busy preparing the release
of our literary portfolios.

297
00:17:18,871 --> 00:17:20,664
And every meeting we have,

298
00:17:21,665 --> 00:17:24,126
every members complete, except one.

299
00:17:25,169 --> 00:17:26,169
Our writer...

300
00:17:27,296 --> 00:17:28,839
Miss Camille Delgado.

301
00:17:30,090 --> 00:17:31,090
Actually...

302
00:17:31,884 --> 00:17:34,094
we haven’t seen her in a long time.

303
00:17:35,272 --> 00:17:36,273
So...

304
00:17:38,015 --> 00:17:39,725
do you think someone abducted her?

305
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:44,813
I don’t initially want to consider
abduction just yet.

306
00:17:45,314 --> 00:17:48,150
More like, something strange is happening.

307
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:50,402
The situation is weird.

308
00:17:50,986 --> 00:17:52,988
Even if she doesn’t show herself to us,

309
00:17:53,197 --> 00:17:57,910
she still finds ways
to submit poems for our portfolio.

310
00:17:58,594 --> 00:18:00,554
And if I remember correctly,

311
00:18:00,579 --> 00:18:02,873
we also asked her via email

312
00:18:02,898 --> 00:18:04,929
why she stopped attending
her meetings, right?

313
00:18:04,954 --> 00:18:05,967
Yeah.

314
00:18:05,992 --> 00:18:10,288
She told us
there’s nothing to worry about.

315
00:18:10,964 --> 00:18:12,508
Maybe she’s sick?

316
00:18:12,841 --> 00:18:15,511
You’d think we didn’t initially
consider that already?

317
00:18:16,028 --> 00:18:17,112
We found out

318
00:18:17,137 --> 00:18:21,809
she didn’t tell
any professors or blockmates

319
00:18:21,834 --> 00:18:24,002
if she was sick.

320
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:28,816
Yet, she still continues
to miss her classes.

321
00:18:29,536 --> 00:18:31,204
Of course that worries us.

322
00:18:31,735 --> 00:18:32,735
Right.

323
00:18:33,362 --> 00:18:37,157
And what’s even weirder
is the poems she wrote.

324
00:18:37,658 --> 00:18:42,204
Because we actually have a theme
that we have to follow for the folio.

325
00:18:42,863 --> 00:18:46,158
But what she submitted
via email is way off

326
00:18:46,333 --> 00:18:48,210
from the category I set.

327
00:18:48,919 --> 00:18:51,463
Have you tried calling her
or going to her house?

328
00:18:51,561 --> 00:18:52,564
Yes.

329
00:18:52,589 --> 00:18:56,093
I’ve called her several times,
but she’s not answering.

330
00:18:56,735 --> 00:18:59,654
I even went to her dorm.

331
00:18:59,760 --> 00:19:02,449
Then I asked her roommates.

332
00:19:02,474 --> 00:19:05,686
But they said she hasn’t been
coming home for days.

333
00:19:06,895 --> 00:19:10,190
Camille’s parents are gone too, so...

334
00:19:10,566 --> 00:19:13,026
There’s nowhere else
she could’ve possibly gone.

335
00:19:13,819 --> 00:19:16,655
Can we see the poems she submitted?

336
00:19:22,077 --> 00:19:24,037
She wrote those poems.

337
00:19:24,955 --> 00:19:27,124
Agatha and I were actually thinking...

338
00:19:27,499 --> 00:19:31,628
our writers' intentions
for submitting poems like that,

339
00:19:32,337 --> 00:19:33,714
it’s gotta be a message.

340
00:19:34,314 --> 00:19:36,567
What kind of message?
We’re not entirely sure.

341
00:19:36,592 --> 00:19:38,392
We haven’t really figured
that out yet, but...

342
00:19:38,719 --> 00:19:40,804
we haven’t really gotten
to that point yet.

343
00:19:40,888 --> 00:19:42,764
That’s why we’re asking you for help.

344
00:19:42,789 --> 00:19:44,791
Hopefully you can help us reveal it.

345
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:47,394
If we’re wrong, of course.

346
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:51,398
"Please don't waste your pity on me

347
00:19:51,982 --> 00:19:54,359
I had enough, I had too much

348
00:19:54,902 --> 00:19:57,738
my heart won't beat, my hand can't touch

349
00:19:58,280 --> 00:20:00,741
Save your pity, there's nothing to see"

350
00:20:01,533 --> 00:20:04,119
"Me and you? Everything is tragedy

351
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:06,997
So why don't you lie on your couch?

352
00:20:07,873 --> 00:20:09,333
Your insincere love

353
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:11,084
That I can no longer vouch

354
00:20:12,044 --> 00:20:13,629
From the shackles of your lust

355
00:20:13,629 --> 00:20:14,630
Set me free"

356
00:20:17,491 --> 00:20:21,633
I don’t know about you,
but these poems are pretty normal to me.

357
00:20:22,232 --> 00:20:26,278
What made you think there was something
unusual about the poems she submitted?

358
00:20:26,642 --> 00:20:28,560
Yes, Lori. It looks normal.

359
00:20:29,162 --> 00:20:30,580
The thing is...

360
00:20:30,812 --> 00:20:34,566
Camille never wrote dramatic poems.

361
00:20:35,083 --> 00:20:38,920
And our theme at the time
is patriotism and horror.

362
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:42,437
She never got our themes wrong before.

363
00:20:43,177 --> 00:20:44,178
I guess you’re right.

364
00:20:44,826 --> 00:20:47,143
Your writer sent an SOS message.

365
00:20:47,390 --> 00:20:48,925
She needs saving desperately!

366
00:20:49,456 --> 00:20:51,291
So, our suspicions were right?

367
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:53,168
Wait, Al.

368
00:20:53,502 --> 00:20:55,796
What makes you think
it's an SOS message?

369
00:20:56,255 --> 00:20:58,966
At first glance,
it looks like an ordinary poem.

370
00:20:59,429 --> 00:21:01,749
And it could've looked like
your writer sent it by mistake.

371
00:21:02,177 --> 00:21:03,720
But the truth is, she didn't.

372
00:21:04,304 --> 00:21:07,391
She sent it to you on purpose
to deliver a hidden message.

373
00:21:08,725 --> 00:21:09,851
Can you give me a minute?

374
00:21:19,569 --> 00:21:22,531
Are you familiar with the different types
of rhyme schemes?

375
00:21:23,573 --> 00:21:25,951
Like the Petrarchan sonnet?

376
00:21:26,785 --> 00:21:27,785
Yes.

377
00:21:28,036 --> 00:21:31,581
We studied that
in high school English class.

378
00:21:32,374 --> 00:21:34,793
Wait, it reminds me of something.

379
00:21:35,419 --> 00:21:39,256
Camille likes using
the Petrarchan sonnet rhyme scheme.

380
00:21:39,568 --> 00:21:41,820
Well, that explains a lot.

381
00:21:42,551 --> 00:21:43,760
She used a technique.

382
00:21:43,969 --> 00:21:46,722
I’m hoping you’ll understand
the message she sent.

383
00:21:47,472 --> 00:21:51,059
A Petrarchan sonnet
follows a specific scheme.

384
00:21:51,601 --> 00:21:55,063
Same rhyme, same letters, same words.

385
00:21:55,731 --> 00:21:56,732
Actually...

386
00:21:58,007 --> 00:22:00,510
It even has a 14-line format.

387
00:22:01,987 --> 00:22:03,989
If I remember correctly, it goes...

388
00:22:04,573 --> 00:22:08,493
A, B, B, A,

389
00:22:09,328 --> 00:22:11,955
A, B, B, A,

390
00:22:12,748 --> 00:22:15,625
C, D, E, C, D, E.

391
00:22:16,126 --> 00:22:18,503
It’s not a copy of the entire format,

392
00:22:18,528 --> 00:22:20,781
but the rhyming scheme's the same.

393
00:22:20,964 --> 00:22:25,969
We label rhyming lines
using letters of the alphabet.

394
00:22:26,678 --> 00:22:28,889
Based on the rhyme scheme
of the first line,

395
00:22:29,681 --> 00:22:31,600
“Please don’t waste your pity on me.”

396
00:22:32,601 --> 00:22:36,897
Fourth and fifth,
“Save your pity, there’s nothing to see.”

397
00:22:37,647 --> 00:22:39,691
“Me and you? Everything is tragedy.“

398
00:22:41,526 --> 00:22:43,987
And the eight line,

399
00:22:44,488 --> 00:22:48,408
all these lines rhyme,
so we’ll label them A.

400
00:22:49,117 --> 00:22:53,830
Second, third, sixth and seventh line,

401
00:22:53,914 --> 00:22:57,959
those lines rhyme, so I’ll label them B.

402
00:22:59,086 --> 00:23:01,296
Now that we know the rhyme scheme,

403
00:23:01,321 --> 00:23:03,865
our next clue
is the titles of the two poems.

404
00:23:04,091 --> 00:23:06,259
And now these are
the most obvious clues.

405
00:23:06,635 --> 00:23:11,890
‘Searching for A’ means we’ll look
at all the lines under the A scheme.

406
00:23:12,599 --> 00:23:15,018
And the next one is the first word.

407
00:23:15,227 --> 00:23:18,688
We’ll look at the first word
of each of these lines.

408
00:23:23,276 --> 00:23:24,276
“Please

409
00:23:24,694 --> 00:23:25,694
save

410
00:23:25,821 --> 00:23:26,821
me

411
00:23:27,030 --> 00:23:28,030
from

412
00:23:28,198 --> 00:23:29,198
my

413
00:23:29,825 --> 00:23:30,825
lover.

414
00:23:31,701 --> 00:23:32,701
His

415
00:23:33,203 --> 00:23:34,203
house."

416
00:23:36,289 --> 00:23:39,876
Please save me from
my lover! His house!

417
00:23:39,901 --> 00:23:40,902
My lover.

418
00:23:41,378 --> 00:23:42,671
Do you know her boyfriend?

419
00:23:42,796 --> 00:23:43,796
Yes!

420
00:23:44,339 --> 00:23:46,258
Mariano… Mariano Lopez.

421
00:23:46,466 --> 00:23:47,884
Do you know where he lives?

422
00:23:47,926 --> 00:23:50,011
Yeah. It’s just near the campus.

423
00:23:50,137 --> 00:23:53,181
I know because I went there
to ask about Camille,

424
00:23:53,432 --> 00:23:55,517
and he told me there’s no problem.

425
00:23:55,542 --> 00:23:58,211
He can still talk to her
and text her.

426
00:23:58,895 --> 00:24:00,647
Well, that makes a lot of sense.

427
00:24:01,731 --> 00:24:04,401
Camille’s probably at his place.

428
00:24:04,876 --> 00:24:06,127
That’s why he’s not worried.

429
00:24:07,279 --> 00:24:08,780
Do we have to call the police?

430
00:24:09,197 --> 00:24:10,198
Not yet.

431
00:24:10,991 --> 00:24:13,952
It’s better if we confirm first

432
00:24:13,977 --> 00:24:15,604
whether Camille is really at his house.

433
00:24:16,496 --> 00:24:17,920
If he's smart enough,

434
00:24:18,123 --> 00:24:23,462
he might’ve realized that the poems sent
were an SOS message.

435
00:24:24,045 --> 00:24:26,548
He might’ve already moved Camille
to another location.

436
00:24:26,798 --> 00:24:28,592
The police’s efforts
would just go to waste.

437
00:24:29,217 --> 00:24:33,805
Or we can try going
to her boyfriend’s house first.

438
00:24:34,573 --> 00:24:36,074
And if it’s confirmed,

439
00:24:36,099 --> 00:24:37,767
we can call the police

440
00:24:37,792 --> 00:24:39,711
and report an abduction at that address.

441
00:24:40,145 --> 00:24:41,480
That’s sounds like a good plan.

442
00:24:41,646 --> 00:24:44,024
We’ll be on standby
and wait your confirmation.

443
00:24:44,566 --> 00:24:46,776
This is the address of Mariano.

444
00:24:48,320 --> 00:24:49,320
Thank you.

445
00:24:52,199 --> 00:24:53,617
Are you still coming with me?

446
00:24:53,992 --> 00:24:55,160
Or should you just stay here?

447
00:24:55,702 --> 00:24:57,037
You might get into trouble, Lori.

448
00:24:57,787 --> 00:24:59,606
Al, remember,

449
00:24:59,789 --> 00:25:02,417
I’m the QED Club’s second-in-command.

450
00:25:02,505 --> 00:25:05,174
Between the two of us,
I should be the one there.

451
00:25:05,545 --> 00:25:07,881
Remember, you’re just an applicant.

452
00:25:09,174 --> 00:25:11,343
Sorry for overstepping, madam.

453
00:25:13,178 --> 00:25:14,178
Okay.

454
00:25:14,304 --> 00:25:15,639
We'll update you.

455
00:25:16,014 --> 00:25:17,014
Okay.

456
00:25:30,737 --> 00:25:32,030
So, let's go?

457
00:25:33,114 --> 00:25:34,157
I've gotta say,

458
00:25:34,407 --> 00:25:36,159
you did really well earlier.

459
00:25:36,801 --> 00:25:39,387
Actually, I feel like
I was really with Loki earlier

460
00:25:39,412 --> 00:25:41,665
with how quick you were able
to decipher that code.

461
00:25:42,082 --> 00:25:43,416
The only difference is

462
00:25:43,708 --> 00:25:46,253
you genuinely care
about the victims and...

463
00:25:46,586 --> 00:25:48,547
you can actually remember their names.

464
00:25:50,298 --> 00:25:51,298
Thank you.

465
00:25:51,716 --> 00:25:53,260
It means a lot coming from you...

466
00:25:53,843 --> 00:25:56,054
Q.E.D.'s second in command.

467
00:25:57,097 --> 00:25:58,181
You're overreacting.

468
00:25:58,532 --> 00:25:59,991
So, let's go?

469
00:26:00,016 --> 00:26:01,560
- Let’s go!
- Let’s go!

470
00:26:06,039 --> 00:26:07,541
Wait, wait. Let me open--

471
00:26:07,566 --> 00:26:09,067
Oh, you're gonna open the door for me.

472
00:26:09,067 --> 00:26:10,569
- Of course.
- What a gentleman.

473
00:26:10,594 --> 00:26:12,137
I always do that, Lori.

474
00:26:33,008 --> 00:26:34,008
Sixty-nine.

475
00:26:43,973 --> 00:26:45,308
Looks like the house is locked.

476
00:26:46,603 --> 00:26:47,826
If we knock,

477
00:26:48,174 --> 00:26:52,136
he'll just refuse to let us in
if Camille's really in there.

478
00:26:57,026 --> 00:26:59,321
Hey! Are you really
going to pick that lock?

479
00:26:59,507 --> 00:27:00,507
Yes.

480
00:27:00,910 --> 00:27:03,669
Lori, are we about to do
something illegal? Huh?

481
00:27:04,414 --> 00:27:05,874
What if someone sees us?

482
00:27:06,374 --> 00:27:08,251
Then we'll be accused of trespassing.

483
00:27:08,460 --> 00:27:11,630
What if Camille needs
immediate medical attention?

484
00:27:15,607 --> 00:27:16,801
Where did you learn that?

485
00:27:17,636 --> 00:27:19,536
Loki taught me how to do this,

486
00:27:19,561 --> 00:27:21,760
in case something like this happens.

487
00:27:22,925 --> 00:27:24,427
I don’t want to do this,

488
00:27:25,021 --> 00:27:26,606
but this is an emergency.

489
00:27:27,796 --> 00:27:28,796
Okay.

490
00:27:29,448 --> 00:27:31,200
Here we go. Let's go.

491
00:27:31,965 --> 00:27:33,675
Let me go first. Okay?

492
00:27:54,923 --> 00:27:55,923
Eat up!

493
00:27:56,555 --> 00:27:57,613
Stop that!

494
00:27:57,926 --> 00:27:59,511
Help me!

495
00:28:01,054 --> 00:28:02,054
Eat.

496
00:28:03,872 --> 00:28:05,541
Look what you did to the food!

497
00:28:07,519 --> 00:28:09,604
You just threw it away, huh?

498
00:28:09,896 --> 00:28:13,316
If you won’t let me go,
just kill me!

499
00:28:16,277 --> 00:28:17,277
Eat up!

500
00:28:18,407 --> 00:28:19,407
Eat!

501
00:28:22,283 --> 00:28:24,035
- Enough!
- Drink.

502
00:28:24,913 --> 00:28:25,956
Drink!

503
00:28:26,287 --> 00:28:28,540
- Enough!
- Drink!

504
00:28:29,499 --> 00:28:31,209
Enough!

505
00:28:38,087 --> 00:28:40,631
You don’t want to eat? Then don’t!

506
00:28:41,761 --> 00:28:44,139
I don’t want to be here anymore!

507
00:28:45,564 --> 00:28:47,358
Help!

508
00:28:50,021 --> 00:28:51,523
Help!

509
00:28:53,231 --> 00:28:54,733
Enough.

510
00:29:02,657 --> 00:29:03,908
You really don’t want to eat?

511
00:29:04,701 --> 00:29:05,910
Enough!

512
00:29:05,994 --> 00:29:06,994
Eat!

513
00:29:07,746 --> 00:29:09,164
I don't want!

514
00:29:12,142 --> 00:29:13,977
Enough! I don't want to!

515
00:29:14,002 --> 00:29:16,807
I told you, you’re mine!

516
00:29:16,838 --> 00:29:19,591
Enough!

517
00:29:20,300 --> 00:29:21,843
- You’re mine!
- Help!

518
00:29:22,802 --> 00:29:24,220
Help!

519
00:29:24,220 --> 00:29:26,347
I told you, no one will hear you!

520
00:29:26,389 --> 00:29:28,558
Help!

521
00:29:29,100 --> 00:29:31,102
Let me go!

522
00:29:32,979 --> 00:29:34,272
Help!

523
00:29:34,297 --> 00:29:36,424
I said, no one will hear you here!

524
00:29:36,983 --> 00:29:39,319
Enough! I don’t want this anymore!

525
00:29:39,486 --> 00:29:40,570
Shut up!

526
00:29:41,154 --> 00:29:42,822
Help!

527
00:29:43,823 --> 00:29:45,742
I don't want this anymore!

528
00:29:47,051 --> 00:29:48,636
You’re mine!

529
00:29:48,661 --> 00:29:50,789
I don't want this anymore!

530
00:29:50,814 --> 00:29:52,816
You don’t want to stay in our house?

531
00:29:53,249 --> 00:29:55,668
Help! I don't want this anymore!

532
00:29:56,309 --> 00:29:58,686
Enough!

533
00:30:00,590 --> 00:30:02,842
- Help!
- There, there.

534
00:30:04,052 --> 00:30:05,303
Whatever!

535
00:30:06,596 --> 00:30:08,473
Help!

536
00:30:09,432 --> 00:30:10,809
Enough.

537
00:30:11,851 --> 00:30:13,812
No one will hear you here!

538
00:30:13,937 --> 00:30:17,857
I don't want this anymore! Help!

539
00:30:18,316 --> 00:30:19,818
You’re so stubborn!

540
00:30:27,283 --> 00:30:28,409
Come on. Hurry.

541
00:30:32,914 --> 00:30:34,415
I don't want this anymore!

542
00:30:35,124 --> 00:30:36,479
My God! Camille!

543
00:30:38,503 --> 00:30:40,338
We need to rush her to the hospital.

544
00:30:40,672 --> 00:30:42,423
Call Augustus and Agatha.

545
00:30:44,843 --> 00:30:45,843
Babe?

546
00:30:50,557 --> 00:30:51,557
Babe?

547
00:30:52,517 --> 00:30:53,977
Babe…

548
00:30:57,313 --> 00:30:58,313
Babe!

549
00:30:59,970 --> 00:31:00,970
Don't!

550
00:31:14,448 --> 00:31:15,574
Agatha!

551
00:31:15,723 --> 00:31:17,475
It's confirmed. Camille's here!

552
00:31:17,500 --> 00:31:18,543
Oh, my God!

553
00:31:24,757 --> 00:31:26,885
She needs urgent medical attention!

554
00:31:27,093 --> 00:31:28,344
Call for help!

555
00:31:28,344 --> 00:31:31,931
- Okay, sure.
- Call an ambulance! Call the police!

556
00:31:40,029 --> 00:31:42,317
It’s okay. I got you. It’s okay.

557
00:32:01,461 --> 00:32:03,296
It’s okay. I got you.

558
00:32:06,299 --> 00:32:07,299
Let's go.

559
00:32:54,430 --> 00:32:55,932
Lori! Get the rope!

560
00:32:55,957 --> 00:32:57,166
Yes, okay.

561
00:33:00,436 --> 00:33:02,605
- You shameless bastards!
- Tie him! Tie him!

562
00:33:02,647 --> 00:33:03,940
Just wait!

563
00:33:03,940 --> 00:33:05,837
- I’m reporting you to the police!
- Tie him up tight!

564
00:33:06,109 --> 00:33:07,777
You should be the one preparing for us!

565
00:33:07,835 --> 00:33:10,880
After what you did to Camille,
we’re sending you to jail!

566
00:33:10,905 --> 00:33:12,425
You’re the ones who should be arrested

567
00:33:12,657 --> 00:33:14,325
for trespassing!

568
00:33:14,659 --> 00:33:15,910
- Trespassing?
- Trespassing?

569
00:33:15,935 --> 00:33:18,730
Did you know saving
your girlfriend’s life exempts us?

570
00:33:18,871 --> 00:33:21,833
Article 280 of the Revised Penal Code!

571
00:33:21,916 --> 00:33:23,668
Don’t interfere!

572
00:33:25,545 --> 00:33:27,088
I’m coming for you!

573
00:33:34,112 --> 00:33:36,072
Let me go! I said let me go!

574
00:33:36,097 --> 00:33:37,598
Explain yourself at the station!

575
00:33:37,974 --> 00:33:38,975
Don't resist!

576
00:33:39,225 --> 00:33:40,810
I’ll remember your faces!

577
00:33:41,310 --> 00:33:42,687
You’ll pay for this!

578
00:33:42,687 --> 00:33:43,687
Take him away!

579
00:33:45,940 --> 00:33:46,940
Take him away!

580
00:33:47,233 --> 00:33:48,233
Come on!

581
00:33:53,239 --> 00:33:54,490
- We'll go ahead.
- Thank you.

582
00:33:55,450 --> 00:33:57,410
- Are you okay?
- Of course.

583
00:34:00,246 --> 00:34:01,706
Lorelei! Alistair!

584
00:34:01,731 --> 00:34:03,149
Gus, Agatha.

585
00:34:03,750 --> 00:34:05,752
I’m very glad
that the two of you are okay.

586
00:34:06,077 --> 00:34:09,205
I personally wouldn’t forgive myself
if anything happens to the two of you.

587
00:34:09,630 --> 00:34:10,882
We’re so glad you’re safe.

588
00:34:11,799 --> 00:34:14,302
Thank you so much
for what you did for Camille.

589
00:34:14,552 --> 00:34:18,389
Don’t worry, we’ll tell her
how you decoded what she wrote.

590
00:34:19,640 --> 00:34:20,683
I hope she’s okay!

591
00:34:21,142 --> 00:34:24,020
- Okay.
- So, we’ll stay with Camille for now.

592
00:34:25,271 --> 00:34:26,564
Thank you! Thank you so much!

593
00:34:26,589 --> 00:34:27,613
- Of course.
- Thank you!

594
00:34:27,638 --> 00:34:29,390
Pleasure doing business
with the both of you.

595
00:34:29,650 --> 00:34:30,985
- Come on.
- Thank you.

596
00:34:31,010 --> 00:34:32,261
Be careful, okay?

597
00:34:36,616 --> 00:34:37,616
Are you okay?

598
00:34:37,825 --> 00:34:38,825
Mm-hmm.

599
00:34:40,578 --> 00:34:43,206
I’m just really curious
about Mariano’s motive.

600
00:34:43,790 --> 00:34:45,875
Let the police investigate that.

601
00:34:46,334 --> 00:34:49,003
The important thing
is we saved the victim.

602
00:34:49,295 --> 00:34:50,880
And we got the culprit.

603
00:34:52,507 --> 00:34:53,507
You’re right.

604
00:34:53,925 --> 00:34:58,179
Actually, I’m planning to talk to Camille
once everything’s okay.

605
00:34:58,827 --> 00:35:02,873
So we can also find out
why her own boyfriend did this to her.

606
00:35:03,684 --> 00:35:05,478
Her story deserves to be told.

607
00:35:06,062 --> 00:35:08,981
So, hopefully,
this won’t happen to anyone else.

608
00:35:09,607 --> 00:35:10,607
I agree.

609
00:35:11,526 --> 00:35:13,528
That’s why there are writers like you.

610
00:35:15,571 --> 00:35:17,532
Thank you, Al.

611
00:35:18,741 --> 00:35:20,493
Good thing you came along.

612
00:35:21,327 --> 00:35:26,249
And you even used
your Taekwondo black belt skills.

613
00:35:28,601 --> 00:35:29,985
I kicked like that.

614
00:35:31,174 --> 00:35:33,005
- I don’t know about you.
- You really are something.

615
00:35:33,910 --> 00:35:34,910
Anytime!

616
00:35:38,113 --> 00:35:40,031
It’s getting late! Let me take you home.

617
00:35:40,195 --> 00:35:43,157
No, it’s okay. I’ll just book a ride.
I can handle it.

618
00:35:43,338 --> 00:35:45,090
No, I insist. Okay?

619
00:35:45,143 --> 00:35:47,103
I’m not letting you go home
without me taking you.

620
00:35:49,349 --> 00:35:50,600
If you say so.

621
00:35:55,036 --> 00:35:56,036
Let's go?

622
00:35:56,460 --> 00:35:57,460
Let's go.

623
00:36:01,402 --> 00:36:03,862
Hey, thanks for bringing me home.

624
00:36:04,392 --> 00:36:06,321
But I’m okay here.

625
00:36:08,374 --> 00:36:10,418
Aren’t you even
going to invite me in?

626
00:36:10,508 --> 00:36:11,843
Or go up to your unit?

627
00:36:14,815 --> 00:36:17,276
After everything we’ve been through
this night,

628
00:36:18,058 --> 00:36:21,812
aren’t you going to invite me in
for coffee or tea?

629
00:36:23,014 --> 00:36:24,140
Just kidding.

630
00:36:24,432 --> 00:36:26,100
Alright, I’ll go now.

631
00:36:28,060 --> 00:36:29,060
Wait.

632
00:36:30,396 --> 00:36:32,067
Maybe you should come upstairs?

633
00:36:33,229 --> 00:36:34,740
We should actually catch up.

634
00:36:35,149 --> 00:36:36,609
It’s been a while so…

635
00:36:37,532 --> 00:36:38,532
Okay.

636
00:36:39,572 --> 00:36:41,657
But before anything else,

637
00:36:42,742 --> 00:36:47,246
there’s something you need to know
about my roommate.

638
00:36:58,925 --> 00:37:00,440
This is the apartment.

639
00:37:05,223 --> 00:37:06,724
Oh, you’re already here.

640
00:37:08,392 --> 00:37:09,810
Good to see you again, Loki.

641
00:37:10,645 --> 00:37:12,146
So you and Lori are roommates?

642
00:37:12,772 --> 00:37:14,815
You didn’t tell me
you’re bringing home a guest.

643
00:37:16,275 --> 00:37:18,027
Nice seeing you again, Altamont!

644
00:37:18,444 --> 00:37:19,444
Alistair!

645
00:37:19,487 --> 00:37:20,947
And he just transferred

646
00:37:20,972 --> 00:37:22,370
- to Clark University.
- Alistair.

647
00:37:22,690 --> 00:37:23,690
Ah!

648
00:37:24,116 --> 00:37:25,159
Your childhood friend.

649
00:37:25,789 --> 00:37:26,789
Mhm.

650
00:37:27,328 --> 00:37:29,080
What a surprising development.

651
00:37:31,832 --> 00:37:36,087
Actually, he helped me solve
a case earlier,

652
00:37:36,112 --> 00:37:38,155
so that’s where we came from.

653
00:37:39,382 --> 00:37:40,382
Interesting!

654
00:37:41,008 --> 00:37:44,303
Care to update me
before the rest of our blog readers?

655
00:37:45,972 --> 00:37:47,807
Well, this is going to be a long story.

656
00:37:48,391 --> 00:37:49,433
Have a seat, Al.

657
00:37:56,415 --> 00:37:58,125
It all started when Agatha brought us

658
00:37:58,150 --> 00:38:01,112
to meet their editor-in-chief,
Augustus Moran.

659
00:38:01,404 --> 00:38:04,198
That’s where we learned
about their missing writer,

660
00:38:04,198 --> 00:38:05,866
Camille Delgado,

661
00:38:05,866 --> 00:38:08,869
and they showed us
her last two submitted poems.

662
00:38:09,495 --> 00:38:14,500
Al decoded it as an SOS message
pointing to her boyfriend Mariano’s house.

663
00:38:15,710 --> 00:38:18,087
Enough! I don't want this anymore!

664
00:38:18,630 --> 00:38:19,709
When we found Camille,

665
00:38:19,814 --> 00:38:22,290
she was imprisoned and badly abused.

666
00:38:24,370 --> 00:38:25,370
Don't!

667
00:38:27,128 --> 00:38:31,289
Fortunately, we managed to rescue her
and called for an ambulance.

668
00:38:32,184 --> 00:38:34,395
- You shameless bastards!
- Tie him! Tie him!

669
00:38:34,420 --> 00:38:35,504
Just wait!

670
00:38:37,732 --> 00:38:40,609
Well, that was quite an adventure.

671
00:38:42,361 --> 00:38:44,238
Good thing you were there, Alistair,

672
00:38:44,488 --> 00:38:48,284
to protect the Q.E.D.'s only Chronicler.

673
00:38:48,951 --> 00:38:52,288
That’s the reason
I entered Clark University.

674
00:38:53,414 --> 00:38:54,832
I’d like to protect Lori.

675
00:38:55,916 --> 00:38:57,168
And in that regard...

676
00:38:58,085 --> 00:39:00,212
I want to apply
to become part of your club.

677
00:39:06,177 --> 00:39:07,177
Well...

678
00:39:07,345 --> 00:39:09,305
I’m currently suspended from school,

679
00:39:10,181 --> 00:39:11,390
and therefore,

680
00:39:11,795 --> 00:39:14,840
from my duties and responsibilities
as club president,

681
00:39:15,027 --> 00:39:17,947
so the decision lies
to the acting president

682
00:39:18,240 --> 00:39:19,741
which happens to be...

683
00:39:20,941 --> 00:39:21,941
Why me?

684
00:39:22,780 --> 00:39:26,951
If for any reason the president
cannot fulfill his duties,

685
00:39:27,901 --> 00:39:30,403
you, the vice president,

686
00:39:31,270 --> 00:39:34,107
will assume the title
and responsibilities.

687
00:39:34,830 --> 00:39:35,830
So...

688
00:39:36,410 --> 00:39:37,703
the decisions is yours.

689
00:39:51,097 --> 00:39:52,431
As acting president,

690
00:39:53,682 --> 00:39:57,478
I accept Alistair's application
into our club.

691
00:40:13,702 --> 00:40:15,996
Welcome to the Q.E.D. Club.

692
00:40:42,575 --> 00:40:45,578
Should we include Jamie or Al,

693
00:40:45,651 --> 00:40:47,859
now that he’s a member
of the Q.E.D. Club?

694
00:40:48,364 --> 00:40:49,615
She's unavailable.

695
00:40:50,714 --> 00:40:53,799
But you can ask your childhood friend
to tag along.

696
00:40:54,201 --> 00:40:56,370
Let them in. I’m with them.

697
00:40:57,788 --> 00:41:00,207
Hi! Hi! Thank you for coming, Loki!

698
00:41:00,541 --> 00:41:02,001
You must be Lorelei?

699
00:41:03,002 --> 00:41:04,266
I'm Herschel Aguirre.

700
00:41:10,176 --> 00:41:12,178
We didn't have time to check the body.

701
00:41:13,012 --> 00:41:16,015
Well, my team immediately
carried him to the clinic.

702
00:41:16,098 --> 00:41:18,267
Or maybe someone injected him
with a needle

703
00:41:18,267 --> 00:41:19,515
laced with curare?

704
00:41:19,540 --> 00:41:20,620
That could be possible too.

705
00:41:20,811 --> 00:41:23,939
But we’ve already checked
all the CCTV footage.

706
00:41:24,023 --> 00:41:27,568
If both or either of the founders
dropped dead later,

707
00:41:27,593 --> 00:41:29,621
this becomes a serial killing.
